<paragraph id="545BC3F753C6B86CAEE4FC27B9F0D3D0" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="165517B4BF40FB58AE4847871A2231AB" LSID="9E779848-E15B-50CC-A6DC-91DED59AEAEA" authority="Dejean, 1821" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Peryphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Peryphus">Peryphus Dejean, 1821</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2178DC8189448EEFAF5CEECEE515EF5" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B32616B0CD32C673347A0233A081637F" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">
<taxonomicName id="0D9FC6DAC7C388BB772ACE5FBEA5842D" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peryphus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1821: 17. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="32BBC19742B7D916A9A7DE8C52843400" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis id="F9E63E0159021C7F0A4C965377509888" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Carabus littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Olivier, 1795 (= 
<taxonomicName id="36FDAE3001E5CEBD83DC448F83E970D2" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracolum">
<emphasis id="1ED9A4F1ED1C5865036362035F0D1C90" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidium tetracolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823) designated by Westwood (1838: 7). Etymology. Possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="9372E828B85235077BA54D993755FB7E" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">peri</emphasis>
(very) and 
<emphasis id="E09F50D74C1568C52469C965AF73378E" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">phos</emphasis>
(light, by extension bright, clear) [masculine]. The name was proposed by Johann Karl Megerle von 
<normalizedToken id="5B2BC503C956FCB3EE9C72FD6538BD96" originalValue="MÃ¼hlfeld">Muehlfeld</normalizedToken>
and made available by Dejean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B6407B35CF117EDA49638A477A92F589" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="51478A60C435871F608B867E4F9267A1" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC8FE375B7E6E830B1CDBA8FD0F597A7" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">
About 65 species in the Nearctic (21 species, three of them adventive), Neotropical (four species in Middle America shared with North America), Palaearctic (about 50 species), and Afrotropical (one species in Ethiopia, 
<taxonomicName id="109BA71D6A29CEDD96225E2993D38689" authorityName="Netolitzky" authorityYear="1937" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scottustulatum">
<emphasis id="08D3929D58D64BF4C1CD4B53EF8CEF12" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion scottustulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Netolitzky) Regions. Three species (
<taxonomicName id="0D3265878FD2F02C92A646612263C933" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1844" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dauricum">
<emphasis id="691EB967464AC4CE90FCC0E1376F67B0" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion dauricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3FEECDAA1B68482D085D17E428E82021" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurellum">
<emphasis id="03D5C3631C657897C75DB02011E39249" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion obscurellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1AE867C6831A99514A8B1F023B37B602" authorityName="Gebler" authorityYear="1833" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrosum">
<emphasis id="3B483770F8E5B777FF2F106E2CE35D00" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion petrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are Holarctic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FF4231D46777C970BC67C2E9565661B4" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" type="identification">
<paragraph id="3EF0674931FF595B68F4FB6863A5B70D" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AEE59219986B58E7A6B61FC4758E0976" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">
Lindroth (1963b: 330-342, as 
<emphasis id="C74CF9E8007100AD4FE5E84B87579BDE" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">tetracolum</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="68889899DF05B5ED8DD2BA8922ADC218" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">transversale</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="3FFBC8E0C493F8DD36FCA607C0F834F2" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">striola</emphasis>
, and in part 
<emphasis id="509D48C5A86ECF64510302551CE9F2D0" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">grapei</emphasis>
groups) covered all but six (
<taxonomicName id="9897251E5C55FEFE02F2A30420BC9CEF" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubre">
<emphasis id="EF78A1804BFBA7A797BA4A3112D3C3B2" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion lugubre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4ED519DFD8290502E2BFCC53DEEDD5A7" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pernotum">
<emphasis id="5D0479D14F7A532E24D17B1F114CAE13" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion pernotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4094AB5F75FAD0F40357C3F3158785EB" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="3C7546853210DC957B41DBE566C899C9" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="76E0BD26D003F404BA1667950BB01D61" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicuum">
<emphasis id="2885570B9BFE8DE7862AADC151ECFC10" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion perspicuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="178C86B2B1D3DA592DA083E8F1622569" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarpedon">
<emphasis id="D4AD2CDF43007859CE73EC047F476B04" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion sarpedon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B32F8AF8E816282F9E0D2586E40CE133" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratum">
<emphasis id="9F77030F70A41FD72F276760DF623D99" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Bembidion femoratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) of the species found in North America. Maddison and Swanson (2010: 26-29) briefly discussed the status of each species of the 
<emphasis id="AE627AED17D070F5A79FA5BF5A2F4716" italics="true" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">transversale</emphasis>
group but did not include a key to separate all species.
</paragraph>
